@Node "Introduction"

   Version 2.6 of an ARexx bridge library to miamibpf.library.
   Just few functions defined, but they do their job pretty good.
   miamibpf.library is a packets filter API for Miami.
   Read miamibpf.library and miamipcap.library autodocs for details.

   All resources created are automagically freed at the exit of the macro.
@EndNode


@Node "Installation"

   To install the library:

   - copy rxmiamibpf.library.library to LIBS:
   - write in a shell: rx "call addlib('rxmiamibpf.library',0,-30)"
   - copy rxsocket.library to LIBS:

   NOTE:
   rxiamibpf.library needs rxsocket.library AmigaDOS shared library API functions.
@EndNode


@Node "Requirements"

   The library needs:
   - Miami (2.xx 3.xx Deluxe) registered   http://www.nordicglobal.com
   - rxsocket.library 	                   Aminet comm/tcp/rxsocket.lha
@EndNode


