@Node "Terms"

   - bpf the unique id returnered by MiamiBPFOpen

   - bpfheaer structure made of
     - SECS
     - MICROS
     - CAPLEN
     - DATELEN
     - HDRLEN
     - PTYPE
     - LTYPE
     - RES
     miamibpf.library attach a 36 bytes header to any packet.
     Real packet is so at offset 36.
     If header in MiamiBPFRead is 0, than a structure bpf header is
     left on the data returned so you will find:
     name      offset
     ----------------
     SECS      0
     MICROS    4
     CAPLEN    8
     DATALEN  12
     HRLEN    16
     PTYPE    20
     LTYPE    21

   - filter the unique id returned by CreateFilter

   - filterstring  a pcap filter string i.e. those passed to miamitcpdump

   - stem or stemName: a valid ARexx variable name e.g. var, var.0, var.name, var;

   - stat set by MiamiPCapStat is a structure with the fields:
     - RECV
     - DROP

   - timeval structure made of
     - SECS
     - MICROS
     use the rmh.library time functions to operate with it

   - types of arguments: the types used are:
     D   any data            --
     N   numeric             /N
     S   symbol              /S ARexx valid symbol
     V   stemName            /V ARexx valid symbol as S but with length<20
@EndNode


