@Node "HELP"
   HELP

   Usage: args=help(funName)
   <funName>

   Returns the arguments types mask of the function funName.
@EndNode


@Node "MIAMIBPFOPEN"
   MIAMIBPFOPEN

   Usage: bpf MiamiBPFOpen(stem)
   <stem/V>

   Create a bpf channel.
   Attributes  are read from stem. They are:
   - BuffLen   the cap buffer - default 256
   - Device    the device to attach the channel on - default "a suitable on" :)
   - TSecs     timeout seconds
   - TMicro    timeout micros
   - Immediate return for each packet incoming - always set it
   - AbortMask abortf signal mask for the channel
   - Filter    a filterstring fro the channel

   Return:
   <0   error may get the reason in BPFSTRING
   >=0  bpf
@EndNode


@Node "MIAMIBPFIOCTLGET"
   MIAMIBPFIOCTLGET

   Usage: res = MiamiBPFIoctlGet(bpf,var,flag)
   <bpf/N>,<var/V>,<flag>

   Read "flag" bpf attribute and write it in var.
   The attributes are:
   - FIONREAD  bpf is read to be read
   - BUFFLEN   cap buff len
   - DEVICE    the device bpf is attached on (just the name not ifr)
   - TIMEOUT   timeout write a timeval in var
   - STAT      statistics write a stat in var

   Return an ARexx boolean.

   NOTE:
   So much to do in this function.
@EndNode


@Node "MIAMIBPFIOCTLSET"
   MIAMIBPFIOCTLSET

   Usage: res = MiamiBPFIoctlSet(bpf,stem)
   <bpf/N>,<stem/V>

   Setbpf attributes from a stem.
   The attributes are:
   - BuffLen   the cap buffer - default 256
   - Device    the device to attach the channel on - default "a suitable on" :)
   - TSecs     timeout seconds
   - TMicro    timeout micros
   - Immediate return for each packet incoming
   - AbortMask abortf signal mask for the channel
   - Filter    a filter string (as in  miamitcpdump) for the channel
   - Flush     flush datas.

   Return an ARexx boolean. on failure may bpfERR is an error string.

   NOTE:
   So much to do in this function.
@EndNode


@Node "MIAMIRXBPFCLOSE"
   MIAMIRXBPFCLOSE

   Usage: call MiamiRXBPFClose(id)
   <id/N>

   Close any object created in this library (actually bpf and filter).

   Always return 1.
@EndNode


@Node "MIAMIBPFSIGNALMASK"
   MIAMIBPFSIGNALMASK

   Usage: res = MiamiBPFSignalMask(bpf)
   <bpf/N>

   Return the signal of the bpf to wait for.
@EndNode


@Node "MIAMIBPFSETABORTMASK"
   MIAMIBPFSETABORTMASK

   Usage: call MiamiBPFSetAbortMask(pcap,signals)
   <bpf/N>,<signals/N>

   Set the abort signals for the bpf.

   Always return 1.
@EndNode


@Node "MIAMIBPFREAD"
   MIAMIBPFREAD

   Usage: len = MiamiBPFRead(bpf,buf,header)
   <bpf/N>,<buf/V>,<0|1>

   Read from a bpf. The function first tries a FIONREAD and then read.
   Write the data in buf.
   If header is 1 the data are returned with the bpfheader.
   If ehader is 0 the data are returned without the bpf header
   which is written in buf.

   To read packet from a bpf you must:
   - set the abort mask for the bpf
   - get the bpf signal
   then:
   - check for FIONREAD (1)
   - if there are datas, ok read them
   - if not wait for the bpf signals (and your signal)
   - goto (1) (yup check again)

   Warning: if you don't set CTRL_C (2**12 in ARexx) as a bpf break signal
            a CTRL-C will not break your macro.

   Returns:
   <0 error or abortmask
    0 timeout
   >0 len of data
@EndNode


@Node "MIAMIBPFFILTER"
   MIAMIBPFFILTER

   Usage: res = MiamiBPFFilter(bpf,filter,packet)
   <bpf/N>,<filter/N>

   Apply a filter on a packet.
   The packet must be read from MiamiBPFRead() with header 0.
   Don't play with it, passign stupid packet. There is no way
   to unsure you are not doing stupid things:
   PASS REAL PACKET READ BY MIAMIBPFREAD WITH HEADER 0.
   I tried to make it crash...not easy but possible.

   Return an ARexx boolean.
@EndNode


@Node "CREATEFILTER"
   CREATEFILTER

   Usage filter = CreateFilter(bpf,filterstring)
   <bpf/N>,<filterstring>

   Create a pcap filter from e.g. the filter string passed to miamitcpdump.
   bpf must be a valid bpf 'cause the funcion needs to know the interface
   the filter is made for.

   Returns:
    <0  failure, the cause string may be in BPFERR
   >=0  filter id to use with MiamiBPFFilter
@EndNode

@Node "Changes"

   - changes from versions < 2.6:
